flow_state|05_Context|Flow State|Flow State describes the conditions under which attention becomes absorbed, effort feels steady, and progress starts to feel self-sustaining.|This domain looks at the conditions that make useful work easier to enter and easier to keep going across focus, ideas, movement, and conversation.|Read the ranked signals as likely flow conditions, not as a fixed identity. Lower-ranked signals are range to use deliberately, not weaknesses.|This is a ranked reading of the conditions most likely to help flow start, deepen, reset, and become useful.|active|flow_state::intro
06_Orientation
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|rank_1_signal_key|rank_2_signal_key|rank_3_signal_key|rank_4_signal_key|orientation_title|orientation_summary|score_shape_summary|rank_1_phrase|rank_2_phrase|rank_3_phrase|rank_4_phrase|status|lookup_key
flow_state|creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|concentrated|creative_movement|deep_focus|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|Creative movement first|Start by looking at Creative movement. Bring in a way to pause, concentrate, and make the work more substantial when the work needs more range.|One signal is doing most of the work here. Creative movement is the clearest starting point for this result.|Your main route is ideas, expression, and new possibilities.|What gives it depth: focused time with one demanding problem.|What helps you reset: movement, pace, and a change of physical state.|What to use deliberately: conversation and feedback before the work becomes too private.|draft|flow_state::creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::concentrated
07_Recognition
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|rank_1_signal_key|rank_2_signal_key|rank_3_signal_key|rank_4_signal_key|headline|recognition_statement|recognition_expansion|status|lookup_key
flow_state|creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|concentrated|creative_movement|deep_focus|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|Original ideas with enough focus to land|You are most likely to find flow when ideas can move, connect, and turn into a direction worth following.|This pattern often shows up when you need room to explore before the work becomes fixed. You may sketch a rough version, try a less obvious angle, or notice links that other people have not seen yet. Deep Focus then helps you stay with the strongest idea long enough to make it useful. Physical Rhythm can clear space when too many possibilities start to crowd the work. Social Exchange becomes useful when the idea needs to be tested with another person.|active|flow_state::creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::concentrated
08_Signal_Roles
domain_key|signal_key|signal_label|rank_position|rank_role|title|description|productive_expression|risk_pattern|development_note|status|lookup_key
flow_state|creative_movement|Creative Movement|1|dominant|Creative Movement as the starting point|Creative Movement is where this pattern usually begins. Flow is most likely when ideas can shift, combine, and find a less obvious way forward.|This can help you generate original possibilities, reframe stuck work, and bring life to something that feels too fixed.|The risk is opening more options after the work needs a clearer decision or a finished version.|Give ideas room early, then choose the strongest direction before the work becomes crowded.|active|flow_state::creative_movement::1
flow_state|deep_focus|Deep Focus|2|secondary|Deep Focus as the source of substance|Deep Focus helps the best idea become useful. It gives the pattern enough patience, depth, and concentration to move beyond a promising first thought.|This can turn creative movement into work with weight, detail, and follow-through.|The risk is waiting too long to focus because the next possibility still feels interesting.|Use focus to hold the best idea still long enough to test and improve it.|active|flow_state::deep_focus::2
flow_state|physical_rhythm|Physical Rhythm|3|tertiary|Physical Rhythm as a practical clear-out|Physical Rhythm helps when ideas become busy, cluttered, or too mental. Movement, pace, or a change of setting can make the next step easier to see.|This can help you reset without shutting down the creative process.|The risk is staying in your head when the work needs a change of state.|Use movement when the work has too many live options and no clear next action.|active|flow_state::physical_rhythm::3
flow_state|social_exchange|Social Exchange|4|least_expressed|Social Exchange as useful outside testing|Social Exchange may not be your first way into flow, but it can help when an idea needs to land outside your own process.|This can help you check whether the idea is clear, relevant, and useful to someone else.|The risk is developing the idea privately after it already needs a response from another person.|Invite one useful person to test the idea before you expand it again.|active|flow_state::social_exchange::4
09_Pattern_Mechanics
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|rank_1_signal_key|rank_2_signal_key|rank_3_signal_key|rank_4_signal_key|mechanics_title|core_mechanism|why_it_shows_up|what_it_protects|status|lookup_key
flow_state|creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|concentrated|creative_movement|deep_focus|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|Why ideas need a useful landing point|This pattern works by letting possibilities open before narrowing them into something usable. Creative Movement creates the range, Deep Focus gives the best idea substance, Physical Rhythm clears clutter, and Social Exchange tests whether the idea lands.|It may show up because new angles feel energising and help the person find a way into the work. The work can feel more alive when it is allowed to move before it is fixed.|It protects originality, flexibility, and the ability to find unexpected routes into progress. The trade-off is that a decision or external test can arrive later than it needs to.|active|flow_state::creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::concentrated
10_Pattern_Synthesis
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|rank_1_signal_key|rank_2_signal_key|rank_3_signal_key|rank_4_signal_key|synthesis_title|gift|trap|takeaway|synthesis_text|status|lookup_key
flow_state|creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|concentrated|creative_movement|deep_focus|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|Possibility that becomes useful work|You can find original possibilities and give the best ones enough focus to matter.|You may keep opening new angles when the work now needs a decision, feedback, or finishing.|Choose the strongest idea sooner, then test it before expanding it again.|This pattern is strongest when creative movement produces options without losing the need for substance. Deep Focus helps you stay with the best direction long enough to improve it. Physical Rhythm gives you a way to clear mental clutter when too many ideas are active. Social Exchange adds the outside response that helps the idea become more useful beyond your own process.|active|flow_state::creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::concentrated
